    <title>Ta-Nehisi Coates is writing a new Superman film produced by J.J. Abrams</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Congressional Hearing On Reparations" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/e-By5fWkXbyBRhZ4aZmk2hZ2lHY=/0x0:2738x1825/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/68881371/1151068320.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Photo by Cheriss May / NurPhoto via Getty Images&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="F1d7vJ"&gt;Celebrated author and essayist Ta-Nehisi Coates is writing a new Superman film that will be produced by J.J. Abrams, &lt;a href="https://shadowandact.com/ta-nehisi-coates-superman-dc-warner-bros-film"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Shadow and Act &lt;/em&gt;reports&lt;/a&gt;. The project has no release date or director attached yet, and there’s still no word on whether Henry Cavill will reprise his role. &lt;em&gt;Shadow and Act &lt;/em&gt;suggests a search for a new actor to play Kal-El / Clark Kent / Superman has yet to begin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="NQZtbY"&gt;Coates is perhaps best known for his books &lt;em&gt;Between the World and Me &lt;/em&gt;and &lt;em&gt;The Beautiful Struggle&lt;/em&gt;, but he also has comics experience, writing popular runs on both &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2016/4/4/11360078/black-panther-marvel-comics-ta-nehisi-coates-brian-stelfreeze"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Black Panther&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/02/we-who-love-america/553991/"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Captain America&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;Coates is also working on several other in-development film and television projects, including &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fbooks%2Fpage-turner%2Ftelling-the-story-of-civil-rights-a-conversation-in-baltimore&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2021%2F2%2F26%2F22303272%2Fsuperman-film-ta-nehisi-coates-new-actor-warner-abrams" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;a television series for HBO&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://www.avclub.com/ryan-coogler-michael-b-jordan-and-ta-nehisi-coates-a-1823225233"&gt;a feature film adaption&lt;/a&gt; of a &lt;em&gt;New Yorker&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2014%2F07%2F21%2Fwrong-answer&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2021%2F2%2F26%2F22303272%2Fsuperman-film-ta-nehisi-coates-new-actor-warner-abrams" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;article...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2021/2/26/22303272/superman-film-ta-nehisi-coates-new-actor-warner-abrams"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
